DISCUSSION
----------
In this experiment, a 4-bit Synchronous Up Counter and a 4-bit Synchronous Up/Down Counter were successfully designed using VHDL and simulated using GHDL. The designs use behavioral VHDL description with process blocks sensitive to the rising edge of the clock (rising_edge(CLK)).

The numeric_std library is utilized to declare counter registers as unsigned vectors, allowing arithmetic operations (+ and -) to perform count increments and decrements directly. Active-high synchronous reset is prioritized at the active clock edge to clear the counter to "0000".

The simulation verified that the Up Counter successfully counts up sequentially. The Up/Down counter successfully counts up while the control input UP is high, counts down when UP is low, and resets synchronously when RST is high.

CONCLUSION
----------
Synchronous Up and Up/Down counter circuits were successfully implemented in VHDL and verified using GHDL simulation. The waveforms demonstrated precise operation matching theoretical state progressions and control input transitions. This experiment enhanced our understanding of sequential design, synchronous control signals, clocking, and register operations using the numeric_std library in VHDL.
